metadata.name: Digital Lava Lamp #203
metadata.description:
All primary sales are donated to @threejs
Best viewed on a decent GPU for 60FPS rendering

In celebration of the anniversary of fxhash, here is a playful interactive simulation, that attempts to replicate the feeling of an abstract lava lamp in a digital world.

[ Controls ]
Play with the physics by dragging your cursor/finger...
Or let the simulation do its thing by staying outside of the frame

[ f ] - fullscreen
[ s ] - save an image
[ r ] - restart the simulation

Created with Three.js + rapier.js

metadata.name: Kinetic Bug #190
metadata.description:
Best viewed on a decent GPU,  because physics simulations are performance intensive. Otherwise you might encounter a bug...

In a world of digital data, a new life is born. We are not alone...
Explore how kinetic bugs make their way through the world. What will their destiny be?
It's curious that we can sympathize to a predefined creature living it's predestined life in the digital world. Coding in the computer abyss reveals interesting worlds.

Keyboard
[ space ] - jump
[ click ] - increase velocity briefly
[ r ] - restart simulation
[ s ] - save image
[ f ] - full screen

Mobile
[ two finger tap ] - jump
[ tap ] - increase velocity briefly

Created with Three.js + rapier.js
Copyright (c) July 2022 Shaderism

metadata.name: Eyeshadow Roses #585
metadata.description:
"Eyeshadow Roses" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

Painterly roses randomly overprinted with heavy streaks of ink. 

The roses grow by a sequence of three spirals, every new spiral smaller and superimposed on the former.  After the roses are fully formed, a random mask of heavy ink is algorithmically screened over the flowers in a pattern of horizontal or vertical lines, occasionally fully flooding the painting. The accumulation of choices evokes graffiti or printmaking. The sequence of choices are interpreted by the computer according to the algorithm. The beauty of these choices are determined by the viewer.

Each piece takes roughly 10 seconds to generate.

Artist: @sarah_ridgley
Press [s] to save the image
JavaScript / p5js | script size: 11kb

metadata.name: Manu #18
metadata.description:
Manu
---------------

A collector-led exploration of minimalist imperfect line work.

Outputs are generated from a combination of the minter's address, their choice from one of 50 seeds, and options to adjust how the generated surface is presented.

Palettes are named after native New Zealand birds and range from the subdued to the colorful.

There are no especially rare traits so mint what you love :)

---------------

Controls:
S - Export as png
H - Toggle high resolution

metadata.name: Strata #7
metadata.description:
A generative series inspired by the work of Vera Molnár, Strata explores the diversity that can come from one shape - the simple rectangle.

With 16 properties and ~600 palettes, I hope that each mint offers something unique and special.

Exploration is fully open and will be left open post-mint :)
